                        Fronttalk Defines:  INDXMSG

Usage:  DEFINE INDXMSG "<string>"

The INDXMSG define is a conference separator displayed when a user does
"DISPLAY INDEX".  It normally just displays the index file.

For full details on its format, see help pages on SEPARATORS, CONFFUNC,
CONFCOND, and SEPDATE.

The default value is:

   "%(1x%2g%)%c"

This just displays the conference index file.
